[assistant] Built a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with a USB-C power/data port, RP2040 MCU, 12 MHz crystal network, decoupling, RUN pull-up, a GPIO25 status LED, and two breakout headers for common GPIO exposure.

- The board uses only local/JLC-imported parts from `imports/RP2040.tsx`, `imports/TYPE_C_16PIN_2MD_073_.tsx`, `imports/XL_1608SYGC_06.tsx`, `imports/A_0603WAF5101T5E.tsx`, `imports/A_0603WAF1001T5E.tsx`, `imports/CL05B104KO5NNNC.tsx`, `imports/X322512MSB4SI.tsx`, `imports/A_0402CG270J500NT.tsx`, and `imports/RC0402FR_0710KL.tsx`, with no tscircuit registry components added.
- Autorouting is disabled at the board level with `routingDisabled`, while electrical connectivity is still described with explicit `trace` elements and named nets.
- I assumed a minimal USB-powered breakout without external flash, SWD header, or a separate 3.3 V regulator, using the imported RP2040 symbol/footprint and its internal regulation pins for a compact demonstration design.
- Generated build output with `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript`, which produced `dist/index/circuit.json` and the site output in `dist/`.
- Generated snapshot artifacts with `tsci snapshot`, which produced `__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg` and `__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg`.
